    "architecture_pattern": "Hybrid file-based + HTTP API — Dashboards primarily read local JSON files via polling; real-time events via WebSocket; no dashboard directly queries a database",
    "data_flow_summary": "UI (file:// polls) → JSON registry files + (fetch/WS) → HTTP APIs → PostgreSQL (bridgedb) or in-memory state",
    "notes": [
      "Most BridgeAI registry dashboards use file:// protocol — will break in any hosted deployment",
      "Port 3000 conflict: topology.html and Xcontainerx BOTH connect to ws://localhost:3000/terminal",
      "Orchestrators L1/L2/L3 form a control plane with no dashboard interface — invisible to operators",
      "Revenue/billing endpoints on ainode exist but are completely unexposed to any UI",
      "File-based state (mesh.json, nodes.json) polled every 2-5s but no server writes them — source unclear",
